Rating: 4
I make this all the time, using baby carrots. It only dirties one pan (unlike traditional glazed carrots) and is quick and tasty. I often put all the ingredients in the pan and place it on the stove earlier in the day. Then, all I have to do when getting the meal together is turn on the stove , check it a few times, and then remove the cover for a few minutes - instant awesome side dish.

Rating: 4
I have made this dish at least 30 times over the past two years for holidays and everyday dinners. Everyone always asks for the recipe and my family requests it at every holiday. The only thing I have found is that I remove the carrots when they are done and reduce the sauce over higher heat so that it resembles more of a thick glaze. I then put the carrots back in, stir and serve. Awesome.

