Rating: 3
The glaze for these carrots gives them a nice holiday taste. I use the same glaze on sweet potatoes but I do cheat. I steam the carrots or boil the potates the day before I use them then make the glaze and reheat the vegetable in it before serving. They taste great and the last minute prep is a lifesaver when preparing a big meal.

Rating: 4
This has been a family favorite since I first made it. One time that I made it, I had run out of pure maple syrup--so I used Aunt Jemima pancake syrup--boy, did that improve the taste!!! A much sweeter, maple taste. Since I use the baby carrots, I reduce the amount of water to just a couple of tablespoons--the prepared carrots seem to have too much water in them, which takes the glaze longer to cook than what the recipe calls for. My daughter requests this dish at every holiday meal and guest dinners!

